<subSubSection id="7A7B8CD31AF4116FDB43D5BC38726BE8" pageId="null" pageNumber="677" type="description">
<paragraph id="5F0E2B49CB9C1D144362198BE247CAE4" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">
Bis 1 m hoch. 
<emphasis id="AA40145867687EF52822F22C46A0E3C9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Rhizom im Schlamm weit kriechend.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="314CC7E1C9E8C21D80F99FCAD83F5A8F" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
bis 15 cm lang, 
<normalizedToken id="41F2E9747FC66279796867069CDB3380" originalValue="1½" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">11/2</normalizedToken>
-2mal so lang wie breit. Blattstiel ⅓-⅕ so lang wie die Spreite. 
<emphasis id="CE453CCC9FB8805806FFF4D7A42F7E8E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">
<normalizedToken id="7A813E39D05B9185A451CB30613EC5DF" originalValue="Staubfäden" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Staubfaeden</normalizedToken>
die Narben weit 
<normalizedToken id="3498764FE3D0C33369332A00E01BB3D1" originalValue="überragend" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">ueberragend</normalizedToken>
.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="885E727F0EF73421B7C6164203D3DD0C" originalValue="Ähre" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Aehre</normalizedToken>
zur Fruchtzeit 10-30 cm lang. - 
<normalizedToken id="96801E84C79DEAB05D12D7271152DB7A" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer; 
<normalizedToken id="6FB214B8C2016EDA53497F96CD5CEF2F" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="98B25DC05B7B3C414AF1E08B5CF82A91" originalValue="Früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Frueher</normalizedToken>
Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A71B0229FD2CD4C3BF878F09E8E5C762" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">
<emphasis id="3A28C2DDA70B183CA3577EB7BDEDA26C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 22:</emphasis>
Material von 12 Fundstellen in Nordamerika; Meiose normal (Baldwin und Speese 1949).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0DCE4789E0ADAA869DA91053453B03E7" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">
<emphasis id="89E31468C2999CC16D79598FB902CAF0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. 
<normalizedToken id="FA30A2FDA81443744250DA0CEB21CA9E" originalValue="Schilfgürtel" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Schilfguertel</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8FA00BB75E9F1F2EC3FEC784CC83A786" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">
<emphasis id="65EDC88555B30194114C9951A570CCC4" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">Verbreitung. Nordostamerikanische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Von Montreal und Quebec 
<normalizedToken id="0C833ADE6653251634E681ED18181FDA" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Florida und Texas. Verbreitungskarte von Baldwin und Speese 1949. - Im Gebiet an den Seen von Varese, wahrscheinlich 
<normalizedToken id="7C74C9BE4799C1BD6F05131017F8F2F2" originalValue="eingebürgert" pageId="null" pageNumber="677">eingebuergert</normalizedToken>
: Lago di Comabbio; erste Fundstelle in 
<taxonomicName id="F8B19E8CAA4EC5B939B15F85F9F4555F" authority="(Stucchi 1952)" baseAuthorityName="Stucchi" baseAuthorityYear="1952" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Europa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="677" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Europa (Stucchi 1952)</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
